flowchart TD

  A([Start: Client intends to sell investment property])

  A --> B[Collect basic exchange info
  • Client entity
  • Property being sold
  • Expected close date]

  B --> C{Decision: Is a 1031 exchange desired?}

  C -- No --> Z([End: Standard sale process])
  C -- Yes --> D[Engage Qualified Intermediary
  • Open exchange file
  • Sign exchange agreement]

  D --> E[Coordinate sale closing
  • Assign contract to QI
  • Provide escrow instructions]

  E --> F[Close sale of relinquished property
  • Proceeds sent to QI
  • Exchange clock starts]

  F --> G[Identify replacement property options
  • One or more candidates
  • Client submits identification]

  G --> H{Decision: Identification submitted on time?}

  H -- No --> X([End: Exchange fails])
  H -- Yes --> I[Validate identification
  • Matches requirements
  • Confirm receipt]

  I --> J[Enter purchase contract for replacement property]

  J --> K[Coordinate replacement closing
  • Assign contract to QI
  • Prepare funding instructions]

  K --> L[Close replacement property
  • QI releases funds]

  L --> M([End: Exchange completed and documented])
